SIMPLE: shortsighted
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Shortsighted
<hw>Short"sight`ed</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Not
able to see far; nearsighted; myopic. See <er>Myopic</er>, and
<er>Myopia</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Fig.: Not able to look far into futurity; unable to
understand things deep; of limited intellect.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Having little regard for the future;
heedless.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Short"sight`ed*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Short"sight`ed*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Cunning is a kind of <qex>shortsightedness</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Addison.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Short-spoken</ent>⟦br⟧
